Lunchtime review.  Alright, I stopped in over the winter months so I was unable to capitalize on the outdoor seating situation BUT I would definitely return during the warmer months to check out the outdoor scene. So Stone street is super cute, has tons of restaurants that line the street and you have a plethora of options. We went with this one for a business networking lunch and cute decor, good service, and good menu options.  I ordered the Asian Chicken Salad and it was nice - the salad had a good crunch, the chicken was good and the dressing was spicy. I didn't read the menu clearly as I had no idea but it was a pleasant surprise. It simply a good salad, next time I might order the steak salad cause my friend's order came out literally almost perfect!  This is definitely a good lunch place if you are in the wall street area, it does the job but definitely nothing to write home about. Overall prices are about $17+ which is expected for this area.
